<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<poem>
    <metadata>
        <title>EULALIE</title>
        <date>1845</date>
    </metadata>
    <body>
        <stanza>
            <lineBreak>I <verb value="closed">dwelt</verb>
                <adv value="closed">alone</adv></lineBreak>
            <lineBreak><prep value="closed">In</prep> a world of moan,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>And my <noun value="open">soul</noun> was a <adj value="closed"
                    >stagnant</adj> tide,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Till the fair and gentle <persName>Eulalie</persName> became my blushing
                bride--</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Till the yellow-haired young <persName>Eulalie</persName> became my smiling
                bride.</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Ah, less--less bright</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>The <noun value="open">stars</noun> of the night</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Than the eyes of the <adj value="open">radiant</adj> girl!</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>And never a flake</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>That the vapor can make</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>With the moon-tints of purple and pearl,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Can vie with the modest <persName>Eulalie</persName>'s most unregarded
                curl--</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Can compare with the bright-eyed <persName>Eulalie</persName>'s most humble
                and careless curl.</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Now <noun value="closed">Doubt</noun>--now <noun value="closed">Pain</noun></lineBreak>
            <lineBreak><verb value="closed">Come</verb> never again,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>For her <noun value="open">soul</noun> <verb value="open">gives</verb> me sigh for sigh,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>And all day long</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak><verb value="open">Shines</verb>, bright and <adj value="open">strong</adj>,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>Astart√© <prep value="closed">within</prep> the <noun value="open">sky</noun>,</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>While ever to her dear <persName>Eulalie</persName> <verb value="open">upturns</verb> her matron eye--</lineBreak>
            <lineBreak>While ever to her young <persName>Eulalie</persName> <verb value="open">upturns</verb> her violet eye.</lineBreak>
        </stanza>
    </body>
</poem>
